Title: Object: Souvenir d'Egypte
Series: L'Orient pittoresque
Description: Three Egyptian women and children walking into the entrance to a building; at left, a woman holding a pitcher near her shoulder, seen in profile; at centre, a woman holding an infant, a shawl draped over their heads; at right, a woman seen from behind, holding a boy's hand, with an infant on her shoulder; at upper left, part of an ornate window seen; proof before letter. 1851/52 Lithograph
Bibliographic references: IFF / Inventaire du Fonds Français: Bibliothèque Nationale, Département des Estampes (17)
Beraldi 1885-92 / Les Graveurs du dix-neuvième siècle (Vol. II, p. 73)
